ifeSummary":"Lady Margaret Wallace是John Wallace的女儿，于1345年出生。她和Ralph Kayl Sir Metcalfe Of Cornwall至少有1个儿子。"},"hr":{"1345–":"1345.–preminula","1345–Female":"1345.–preminula","1365–1385":"1365.–1385","1365–Male":"1365.–preminuo","1307–Male":"1307–preminuo","1345":"1345.","1365":"1365.","1385":"1385","1307":"1307","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1345–":"1345–Zesnulá","1345–Female":"1345–Zesnulá","1365–1385":"1365–1385","1365–Male":"1365–Zesnulý","1307–Male":"1307–Zesnulý","1345":"1345","1365":"1365","1385":"1385","1307":"1307","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1345–":"1345–Afdød","1345–Female":"1345–Afdød","1365–1385":"1365–1385","1365–Male":"1365–Afdød","1307–Male":"1307–Afdød","1345":"1345","1365":"1365","1385":"1385","1307":"1307","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1345–":"1345–Overleden","1345–Female":"1345–Overleden","1365–1385":"1365–1385","1365–Male":"1365–Overleden","1307–Male":"1307–Overleden","1345":"1345","1365":"1365","1385":"1385","1307":"1307","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1345–":"1345–Deceased","1345–Female":"1345–Deceased","1365–1385":"1365–1385","1365–Male":"1365–Deceased","1307–Male":"1307–Deceased","1345":"1345","1365":"1365","1385":"1385","1307":"1307","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Wallace","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish and English: variant of   Wallis  , especially in Scotland, where the name was introduced from the Welsh Marches by a family of tenants of the Stewarts in the 12th century.","Americanized form of various like-sounding Jewish (Ashkenazic) surnames, e.g.   Wallach  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Walles","meanings":["English: variant of   Wallace  ."]},{"name":"Wallis","meanings":["Scottish and English: from Anglo-Norman French <i>Waleis</i>, <i>Walais</i> ‘Welshman’, also sometimes ‘Breton’ (from Old English <i>wēalas</i>, <i>walas</i>, plural of <i>walh</i>, <i>wealh</i>, originally meaning a ‘Roman citizen’ and referring to the native British population, but in Old English this term later came to mean ‘serf, unfree person, foreigner’ or ‘Welshman’). In western and central England the medieval reference is clearly to Welshmen. In Norfolk and Lincolnshire, the reference was probably to Bretons, many of whom settled in the eastern counties after the Conquest. Compare   Welsh  ,   Walsh  . The idea that the Scottish surname refers to the Welsh-speaking Britons of Strathclyde is erroneous."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Margaret Wallace was born in 1345 as the daughter of John Wallace. She had at least 1 son with Ralph Kayl Sir Metcalfe Of Cornwall."},"et":{"1345–":"1345–Surnud","1345–Female":"1345–Surnud","1365–1385":"1365–1385","1365–Male":"1365–Surnud","1307–Male":"1307–Surnud","1345":"1345","1365":"1365","1385":"1385","1307":"1307","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1345–":"1345–Kuollut","1345–Female":"1345–Kuollut","1365–1385":"1365–1385","1365–Male":"1365–Kuollut","1307–Male":"1307–Kuollut","1345":"1345","1365":"1365","1385":"1385","1307":"1307","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1345–":"1345–Décédée","1345–Female":"1345–Décédée","1365–1385":"1365–1385","1365–Male":"1365–Décédé","1307–Male":"1307–Décédé","1345":"1345","1365":"1365","1385":"1385","1307":"1307","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornouailles, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lady Margaret Wallace est née en 1345, fille de John Wallace. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Ralph Kayl Sir Metcalfe Of Cornwall."},"de":{"1345–":"1345–Verstorben","1345–Female":"1345–Verstorben","1365–1385":"1365–1385","1365–Male":"1365–Verstorben","1307–Male":"1307–Verstorben","1345":"1345","1365":"1365","1385":"1385","1307":"1307","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Lady Margaret Wallace wurde 1345, als Tochter von John Wallace geboren. Sie hatte mit Ralph Kayl Sir Metcalfe Of Cornwall mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1345–":"1345–Desede","1345–Female":"1345–Desede","1365–1385":"1365–1385","1365–Male":"1365–Desede","1307–Male":"1307–Desede","1345":"1345","1365":"1365","1385":"1385","1307":"1307","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Angletè, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"1345–":"1345–elhunyt","1345–Female":"1345–elhunyt","1365–1385":"1365–1385","1365–Male":"1365–elhunyt","1307–Male":"1307–elhunyt","1345":"1345","1365":"136